The paper discusses challenges and new directions in software development for blockchain technology. This topic falls under the software engineering domain, which is covered by cs.SE. The paper also mentions testing activities and security concerns, which are relevant to the sub-category cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The use of smart contracts in blockchain development relates to cs.PL (Programming Languages). The need for collaboration in large teams and the use of distributed systems are relevant to cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
